163union VALUETYPE {
164 uint8_t b;
165 uint16_t h;
166 uint32_t l;
167 uint64_t q;
168 uint8_t hs[2]; /* 2 bytes of a fixed-endian "short" */
169 uint8_t hl[4]; /* 4 bytes of a fixed-endian "long" */
170 uint8_t hq[8]; /* 8 bytes of a fixed-endian "quad" */
171 char s[MAXstring]; /* the search string or regex pattern */
172 unsigned char us[MAXstring];
173 float f;
174 double d;
175};
176
177struct magic {
178 /* Word 1 */
179 uint16_t cont_level; /* level of ">" */
180 uint8_t flag;
181#define INDIR 0x01 /* if '(...)' appears */
182#define OFFADD 0x02 /* if '>&' or '>...(&' appears */
183#define INDIROFFADD 0x04 /* if '>&(' appears */
184#define UNSIGNED 0x08 /* comparison is unsigned */
185#define NOSPACE 0x10 /* suppress space character before output */
186#define BINTEST 0x20 /* test is for a binary type (set only
187 for top-level tests) */
188#define TEXTTEST 0x40 /* for passing to file_softmagic */
189
190 uint8_t factor;
191
192 /* Word 2 */
193 uint8_t reln; /* relation (0=eq, '>'=gt, etc) */
194 uint8_t vallen; /* length of string value, if any */
195 uint8_t type; /* comparison type (FILE_*) */
196 uint8_t in_type; /* type of indirection */
197#define FILE_INVALID 0
198#define FILE_BYTE 1
199#define FILE_SHORT 2
200#define FILE_DEFAULT 3
201#define FILE_LONG 4
202#define FILE_STRING 5
203#define FILE_DATE 6
204#define FILE_BESHORT 7
205#define FILE_BELONG 8
206#define FILE_BEDATE 9
207#define FILE_LESHORT 10
208#define FILE_LELONG 11
209#define FILE_LEDATE 12
210#define FILE_PSTRING 13
211#define FILE_LDATE 14
212#define FILE_BELDATE 15
213#define FILE_LELDATE 16
214#define FILE_REGEX 17
215#define FILE_BESTRING16 18
216#define FILE_LESTRING16 19
217#define FILE_SEARCH 20
218#define FILE_MEDATE 21
219#define FILE_MELDATE 22
220#define FILE_MELONG 23
221#define FILE_QUAD 24
222#define FILE_LEQUAD 25
223#define FILE_BEQUAD 26
224#define FILE_QDATE 27
225#define FILE_LEQDATE 28
226#define FILE_BEQDATE 29
227#define FILE_QLDATE 30
228#define FILE_LEQLDATE 31
229#define FILE_BEQLDATE 32
230#define FILE_FLOAT 33
231#define FILE_BEFLOAT 34
232#define FILE_LEFLOAT 35
233#define FILE_DOUBLE 36
234#define FILE_BEDOUBLE 37
235#define FILE_LEDOUBLE 38
236#define FILE_BEID3 39
237#define FILE_LEID3 40
238#define FILE_INDIRECT 41
239#define FILE_QWDATE 42
240#define FILE_LEQWDATE 43
241#define FILE_BEQWDATE 44
242#define FILE_NAME 45
243#define FILE_USE 46
244#define FILE_CLEAR 47
245#define FILE_DER 48
246#define FILE_NAMES_SIZE 49 /* size of array to contain all names */
247
248#define IS_STRING(t) \
249 ((t) == FILE_STRING || \
250 (t) == FILE_PSTRING || \
251 (t) == FILE_BESTRING16 || \
252 (t) == FILE_LESTRING16 || \
253 (t) == FILE_REGEX || \
254 (t) == FILE_SEARCH || \
255 (t) == FILE_INDIRECT || \
256 (t) == FILE_NAME || \
257 (t) == FILE_USE)
258
259#define FILE_FMT_NONE 0
260#define FILE_FMT_NUM 1 /* "cduxXi" */
261#define FILE_FMT_STR 2 /* "s" */
262#define FILE_FMT_QUAD 3 /* "ll" */
263#define FILE_FMT_FLOAT 4 /* "eEfFgG" */
264#define FILE_FMT_DOUBLE 5 /* "eEfFgG" */
265
266 /* Word 3 */
267 uint8_t in_op; /* operator for indirection */
268 uint8_t mask_op; /* operator for mask */
269#ifdef ENABLE_CONDITIONALS
270 uint8_t cond; /* conditional type */
271#else
272 uint8_t dummy;
273#endif
274 uint8_t factor_op;
275#define FILE_FACTOR_OP_PLUS '+'
276#define FILE_FACTOR_OP_MINUS '-'
277#define FILE_FACTOR_OP_TIMES '*'
278#define FILE_FACTOR_OP_DIV '/'
279#define FILE_FACTOR_OP_NONE '\0'
280
281#define FILE_OPS "&|^+-*/%"
282#define FILE_OPAND 0
283#define FILE_OPOR 1
284#define FILE_OPXOR 2
285#define FILE_OPADD 3
286#define FILE_OPMINUS 4
287#define FILE_OPMULTIPLY 5
288#define FILE_OPDIVIDE 6
289#define FILE_OPMODULO 7
290#define FILE_OPS_MASK 0x07 /* mask for above ops */
291#define FILE_UNUSED_1 0x08
292#define FILE_UNUSED_2 0x10
293#define FILE_OPSIGNED 0x20
294#define FILE_OPINVERSE 0x40
295#define FILE_OPINDIRECT 0x80
296
297#ifdef ENABLE_CONDITIONALS
298#define COND_NONE 0
299#define COND_IF 1
300#define COND_ELIF 2
301#define COND_ELSE 3
302#endif /* ENABLE_CONDITIONALS */
303
304 /* Word 4 */
305 int32_t offset; /* offset to magic number */
306 /* Word 5 */
307 int32_t in_offset; /* offset from indirection */
308 /* Word 6 */
309 uint32_t lineno; /* line number in magic file */
310 /* Word 7,8 */
311 union {
312 uint64_t _mask; /* for use with numeric and date types */
313 struct {
314 uint32_t _count; /* repeat/line count */
315 uint32_t _flags; /* modifier flags */
316 } _s; /* for use with string types */
317 } _u;
318#define num_mask _u._mask
319#define str_range _u._s._count
320#define str_flags _u._s._flags
321 /* Words 9-24 */
322 union VALUETYPE value; /* either number or string */
323 /* Words 25-40 */
324 char desc[MAXDESC]; /* description */
325 /* Words 41-60 */
326 char mimetype[MAXMIME]; /* MIME type */
327 /* Words 61-62 */
328 char apple[8]; /* APPLE CREATOR/TYPE */
329 /* Words 63-78 */
330 char ext[64]; /* Popular extensions */
331};

333#define BIT(A) (1 << (A))
334#define STRING_COMPACT_WHITESPACE BIT(0)
335#define STRING_COMPACT_OPTIONAL_WHITESPACE BIT(1)
336#define STRING_IGNORE_LOWERCASE BIT(2)
337#define STRING_IGNORE_UPPERCASE BIT(3)
338#define REGEX_OFFSET_START BIT(4)
339#define STRING_TEXTTEST BIT(5)
340#define STRING_BINTEST BIT(6)
341#define PSTRING_1_BE BIT(7)
342#define PSTRING_1_LE BIT(7)
343#define PSTRING_2_BE BIT(8)
344#define PSTRING_2_LE BIT(9)
345#define PSTRING_4_BE BIT(10)
346#define PSTRING_4_LE BIT(11)
347#define REGEX_LINE_COUNT BIT(11)
348#define PSTRING_LEN \
349 (PSTRING_1_BE|PSTRING_2_LE|PSTRING_2_BE|PSTRING_4_LE|PSTRING_4_BE)
350#define PSTRING_LENGTH_INCLUDES_ITSELF BIT(12)
351#define STRING_TRIM BIT(13)
352#define CHAR_COMPACT_WHITESPACE 'W'
353#define CHAR_COMPACT_OPTIONAL_WHITESPACE 'w'
354#define CHAR_IGNORE_LOWERCASE 'c'
355#define CHAR_IGNORE_UPPERCASE 'C'
356#define CHAR_REGEX_OFFSET_START 's'
357#define CHAR_TEXTTEST 't'
358#define CHAR_TRIM 'T'
359#define CHAR_BINTEST 'b'
360#define CHAR_PSTRING_1_BE 'B'
361#define CHAR_PSTRING_1_LE 'B'
362#define CHAR_PSTRING_2_BE 'H'
363#define CHAR_PSTRING_2_LE 'h'
364#define CHAR_PSTRING_4_BE 'L'
365#define CHAR_PSTRING_4_LE 'l'
366#define CHAR_PSTRING_LENGTH_INCLUDES_ITSELF 'J'
367#define STRING_IGNORE_CASE (STRING_IGNORE_LOWERCASE|STRING_IGNORE_UPPERCASE)
368#define STRING_DEFAULT_RANGE 100
369
370#define INDIRECT_RELATIVE BIT(0)
371#define CHAR_INDIRECT_RELATIVE 'r'

373/* list of magic entries */
374struct mlist {
375 struct magic *magic; /* array of magic entries */
376 uint32_t nmagic; /* number of entries in array */
377 void *map; /* internal resources used by entry */
378 struct mlist *next, *prev;
379};

381#ifdef __cplusplus
382#define CAST(T, b) static_cast<T>(b)
383#define RCAST(T, b) reinterpret_cast<T>(b)
384#define CCAST(T, b) const_cast<T>(b)
385#else
386#define CAST(T, b) ((T)(b))
387#define RCAST(T, b) ((T)(uintptr_t)(b))
388#define CCAST(T, b) ((T)(uintptr_t)(b))
389#endif

391struct level_info {
392 int32_t off;
393 int got_match;
394#ifdef ENABLE_CONDITIONALS
395 int last_match;
396 int last_cond; /* used for error checking by parse() */
397#endif
398};
399
400#define MAGIC_SETS 2
401
402struct magic_set {
403 struct mlist *mlist[MAGIC_SETS]; /* list of regular entries */
404 struct cont {
405 size_t len;
406 struct level_info *li;
407 } c;
408 struct out {
409 char *buf; /* Accumulation buffer */
410 char *pbuf; /* Printable buffer */
411 } o;
412 uint32_t offset; /* a copy of m->offset while we */
413 /* are working on the magic entry */
414 uint32_t eoffset; /* offset from end of file */
415 int error;
416 int flags; /* Control magic tests. */
417 int event_flags; /* Note things that happened. */
418#define EVENT_HAD_ERR 0x01
419 const char *file;
420 size_t line; /* current magic line number */
421 mode_t mode; /* copy of current stat mode */
422
423 /* data for searches */
424 struct {
425 const char *s; /* start of search in original source */
426 size_t s_len; /* length of search region */
427 size_t offset; /* starting offset in source: XXX - should this be off_t? */
428 size_t rm_len; /* match length */
429 } search;
430
431 /* FIXME: Make the string dynamically allocated so that e.g.
432 strings matched in files can be longer than MAXstring */
433 union VALUETYPE ms_value; /* either number or string */
434 uint16_t indir_max;
435 uint16_t name_max;
436 uint16_t elf_shnum_max;
437 uint16_t elf_phnum_max;
438 uint16_t elf_notes_max;
439 uint16_t regex_max;
440 size_t bytes_max; /* number of bytes to read from file */
441#define FILE_INDIR_MAX 50
442#define FILE_NAME_MAX 30
443#define FILE_ELF_SHNUM_MAX 32768
444#define FILE_ELF_PHNUM_MAX 2048
445#define FILE_ELF_NOTES_MAX 256
446#define FILE_REGEX_MAX 8192
447};
